==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incasement
<hw>In*case"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Casement</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of inclosing with a case, or the
state of being incased.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which forms a case, covering, or
inclosure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incask</ent>⟦br⟧
